##How did Ms. Huang, who was released after serving her sentence, leave the Han Dynasty and enter Beijing? FIVE QUESTIONS TO ANSWER!

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

How did Ms. Huang and her family "successfully complete the whole process of entering Beijing" ? Are there more "Ms Huang" ? These puzzling questions await the conclusions of the three investigative teams that were swiftly set up within a day, and which are reasonably legitimate to the public.

By Wang Zhongyun Anne

On February 26th Beijing attracted widespread attention when it announced that a confirmed case had returned to Beijing from Wuhan. A newly diagnosed case of pneumonia was reported in Dongcheng District on February 24. The woman came to Beijing from Wuhan on February 22, on the 18th in Wuhan had fever symptoms. Three close contacts have been quarantined.

Subsequently, the Beijing Center for Disease Control and Prevention gave a detailed account of the case: Ms. Huang, February 18 began intermittent fever for five days, accompanied by Pharynx Discomfort, then living in Wuhan. Ms Wong arrived in Beijing by car at 2:00 am on February 22 and checked into her family's home in Xinyi, Dongcheng District. At 19:00 on February 23, Ms. Huang was transferred from the ambulance to the hospital for examination due to fever. A confirmed case of new crown pneumonia was identified on 24 February.

Like the author, I'm sure the first reaction to the news was one of bewilderment: The Li Han corridor was closed over a month ago. In the case of strict control, has been the symptoms of fever, Ms Huang is how to drive out of Wuhan City, and how is all the way back to Beijing?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
North Gate of Xinyi Home Community | governor of Chang'an Avenue

He was released from prison. He was involved in corruption case of water conservancy in Hubei Province

The discussion about Ms Huang's identity began after news of her return to Beijing and her diagnosis spread online. According to netizens, the woman is the second sister of Huang Guangyu, the founder of gome electric appliances, and the second in the family, Huang Yanhong, who was previously the director of the Gome Group Supervision Center. A staff member of the Hubei Provincial Bureau of Prison Administration denied this.

The staff member made it clear that Ms. Huang, who returned to Beijing from Wuhan, was not named Huang Yanhong and was not an ex-gome executive. At the same time, the issue of WHO Ms. Huang really is, has also been gradually disclosed. On CCTV's News 1 + 1 program broadcast on the evening of March 26, host Bai Yansong mentioned that Ms. Huang was an ex convict.

According to the written judgment of that year, it is now known that the woman was born on January 8,1959 in Jianshi County, Hubei Province. She is a college educated woman who was originally the deputy director and cashier of the finance unit of the Water Resources and Aquatic Products Bureau of Xuanen county and lived in Xuan'en County, Hubei Province.

According to the verdict, Yi Mou Fu, the former deputy director of the Xuanen Bureau of Water Resources and aquatic products, Huang Mou Ying, the cashier, and Xia mou yan, the accountant, were state functionaries who, taking advantage of their positions, wantonly embezzled state property. Yi Mou Fu embezzled a total of 481893 public funds, in total, Huang embezzled 721720 yuan, while Xia embezzled 353200 yuan and got 176600 yuan. Their actions constitute a crime of corruption.

On June 21,2013, a court in Xuan'en County, Hubei Province sentenced the defendant, surnamed Huang, to 10 years in prison and confiscation of property of 60,000 yuan for corruption. The defendant, surnamed Wong, lodged an appeal. On 18 February 2014, the Ensch House of Representatives dismissed the appeal and upheld the judgment. Enshi Intermediate Court on March 20,2014, Guan Bo also confirmed that Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture Xuanen County Water Conservancy and Fisheries Bureau "Nest Case" second trial concluded.

While serving his sentence, Huang was commuted twice. In September 2017, Huang was given a seven-month reduction in his sentence, and in August 2019, Huang was given a further eight-month reduction, according to the 2017 Hubei Wuhan Intermediate Court's 2001 E01 criminal conviction No. 2371. His sentence thus runs from 18 April 2011 to 17 February 2020. Huang mou-ying is in this matter of Ms. Huang.

On the afternoon of February 27, Ms. Huang's defense lawyer said in an interview that Ms. Huang's original domicile was in Xuan'en County, Hubei Province, "She was very well connected in Ensch, she managed the small coffers of her former employer, she came from a good family, she owned three apartments, her husband fell ill after becoming paralyzed in 2013 and they were separated. ". Huang "spent more than two years in Ensch" and was sent to Wuhan Women's prison in 2014 after a second trial verdict took effect, her lawyer said.

The defense lawyer said Huang's daughter, Qin, was selling local products in Beijing. This time, Qin and other family members went to Wuhan Women's prison to pick up Huang and return him to Beijing.

To See "Wuhan Women's prison" , it is not difficult to associate a few days ago the news. Hubei had previously notified 3 prisons occurred new pneumonia epidemic, including Wuhan Women's prison. On 11 February, there were 230 cases in the prison, and two days later the number of confirmed cases had increased to 279. Currently, the prison director Zhou Yukun has been removed from office.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There are so many questions that need to be answered

According to details released by CAIXIN, Beijing News and Red Star News, Ms. Huang's residence in Beijing is located in the Xinyi Home District of Chongwenmen Business District, on the edge of Beijing's second ring road, less than 3 kilometers away from Tiananmen Square in a straight line.

Completed in 2004-2006, the complex was one of the few high-end developments in Beijing's southern city at the time, located in the city's bustling Chongwenmen shopping district. There are 8 low-density residential buildings in Xinyijiayuan community, all facing north and south, most of which are more than 100 square meters. The average price is 20,000 yuan / square meters at the opening.

"She had a good financial situation and bought a house for her daughter in Beijing before the accident, " said Huang's lawyer

On the afternoon of the 26th, Wuhan Women's prison staff responded to the media, the prison has not released prisoners recently, the current prisoners are in detention.

That is to say, Ms. Huang is released from prison, but whether it must be released from Wuhan Women's prison? Pending confirmation of further official notification.

The 1,000 km drive from Wuhan to Beijing takes at least 14 hours. Ms. Huang, who was picked up from Wuhan by her family at 2 a.m. on Feb. 22, was supposed to have left Wuhan before 12 noon on Feb. 21.

On February 18, Ms. Huang had a fever that predated her departure, according to the circular. But "we were deceived, " the family said in interviews with the media. One of Ms. Huang's relatives said that after her release from prison, they received a notice from the prison asking them to pick up the person, but did not mention that Ms. Huang had a fever. "What we are doing is both legitimate and legal. We didn't do anything out of line. " "He kept asking us to pick people up, but he lied about the prison, and I didn't know how dangerous it was for us to come back. "

On the way back from Wuhan to Beijing, Ms. Huang's relatives learned of the outbreak at the Wuhan Women's prison.

At noon on the same day in Beijing, the family reported to the community that the Dongcheng District Center for Disease Control and Prevention had placed Ms. Huang and her family in quarantine, and that other family members at her home had been taken away after Ms. Huang was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia on Feb. 24.

On the afternoon of the 27th, Huang's daughter, Qin, said, "I believe the Ministry of Justice will give an impartial investigation. "

The truth is not yet known, and given what we already know, the following questions are likely to stick in people's throats:

1. Ms. Huang's family seems to be cooperating after their return to Beijing. But do they know what a siege is? The literal meaning of the word "lockdown, " okay? The prison let them take him, and they took him away, as if from Wuhan, and then to the capital..

2. On February 18, Ms. Huang had a fever that predated her departure. Family members claim to have been deceived by the prison, regardless of whether the release is Wuhan Women's prison, even if the prison "did not mention the matter of fever" , but before the departure of Ms. Huang had fever, how the family "ignored" it? Coincidence? A Master Plan?

3. How to leave Wuhan, and how to return to Beijing, Ms. Huang's family did not explain. Wuhan closed the city to prevent exports, Beijing stubbornly defend watertight, all the way checkpoints, how can they do in the heat of the case of "break out of the encirclement, come and go freely" ? This is the biggest question mark.

4. During the epidemic, the release of prisoners in Wuhan and Hubei Province also caused widespread concern. What if the person released from prison is not local? How to solve the problem of temporary placement?

5. Are there any more "free-spirited" "Ms Wong" ?

In one day, three investigative teams were formed

In the current critical period of epidemic prevention and control, and the epidemic is still severe in Wuhan, why such an event, naturally quickly become a matter of great concern. In other words, at this point in time, the matter is not clear, not to the public a clear explanation, certainly not.

Within a day, three investigation teams had been set up. On February 26, with the approval of the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission, the Ministry of Justice took the lead, led by Deputy Minister in charge Alan Lowe, and formed a joint investigation team with the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission, the Supreme People's Procuratorate and the Ministry of Public Security, to Hubei Province to investigate the case of a former prisoner of Wuhan women's prison who came to Beijing with new pneumonia.

On February 26,2020, the Commission of Discipline Inspection and supervision of the Beijing Municipal Commission of Discipline Inspection and the Municipal Commission of Supervision of the Beijing Municipal Commission of Discipline Inspection also set up an investigation team, focusing on how Huang entered Beijing and how he entered the community, to investigate whether there were any loopholes in the whole process of epidemic prevention and control.

Similarly, late in the night of February 26, the Hubei Daily issued a message, in response to an online rumor on the 26th that a person who had been released from prison with newly diagnosed pneumonia had arrived in Beijing from the Han Dynasty. The party secretary of Hubei Province, Ying Yong, issued a directive: in the most arduous key stage of the epidemic prevention and control, the occurrence of such serious violations of the Han li-e channel control of the incident must not be allowed. We must promptly ascertain the facts, deal with them seriously in accordance with the law and discipline, and respond to social concerns in a timely manner. Whether or not this matter involves other violations of the law and discipline, we should also thoroughly investigate. No matter WHO's involved, get to the bottom of it. The management and control of the corridor from Han to Hubei is related to the overall situation of national epidemic prevention and control.

Hubei Province has set up a joint investigation team led by the Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision, the Provincial Commission for Political Science and Law, the provincial procuratorate, the provincial public security department and the provincial department of Justice, to carry out investigations immediately.

On a number of puzzling questions, the three teams will return to the public with a reasonable and legal conclusion.
